HEADWORD: Zirconoid
<hw>Zir"con*oid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Zircon</ets>
+ <ets>oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>A double
eight-sided pyramid, a form common with tetragonal crystals; -- so
called because this form often occurs in crystals of
<ets>zircon</ets>.</def>⟦br⟧
